	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> <date>Wednesday December 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1854</date>.</p>
				<p>My dear <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
				<p>We have been anxiously waiting for a letter<lb/> but are disappointed.  Nothing new has occurred<lb/> the Occident came yesterday&#44; two weeks after we<lb/> sent for them&#44; they are ready to send away.  no&#45;<lb/>one has been to inquire after you.  There are a<lb/> few letters coming to the house for you&#44; Mama<lb/> thinks they all know you are absent.  We received<lb/> a letter from <persName>Uncle Sam</persName> on <date>Monday</date>&#44; he says<lb/> Mama had better not move till he comes on next<lb/> summer.  We wish you were back again the wea<lb/>&#45;ther is so extremely cold we are afraid you will<lb/> get sick&#44; it snows and we can hardly keep warm<lb/> I went down to <persName>Mr Martins</persName> dancing school&#44; day before<lb/> yesterday&#44; with Mama&#44; <persName>Mr Hans</persName>&#39; daughters are<lb/> going.  <persName>Delia</persName> is trying to learn to read.  You<lb/> must excuse my short letter for I have my<lb/> lessons to learn.  We have a new girl she came<lb/> on <date>Saturday</date>.</p>
				<p>PS <date>Thursday 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">We received your letter dated the <date>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi></date> in<lb/> the morning and the one dated the <date>7<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> in the afternoon</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>They were both very <sic>ecceptable</sic>.  We will attend to<lb/> the Bible.  There is a <sic>discontinuence</sic> from <placeName>Louisville</placeName><lb/> we have had no letters for you for several days and<lb/> no money.  It will come in bushels when you come<lb/> home <sic>wich</sic> Mama hopes will be very soon<lb/> you must take care of your self and not get frozen<lb/> up.  I will look over the Map and do just as you<lb/> told me&#160;&#160;&#160;Mamas best regards and hopes you<lb/> will take care of your<lb/> <persName>Delia</persName> sends her love</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">This is from your little</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Nelly Cozens</persName></p>
		</body>
